parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Leaks and Sending Unit Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks can cause fires, and faulty sending units can lead to inaccurate fuel level readings, potentially causing accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: especially when the tank is full

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Carburetor problems can cause fires, which can lead to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
Internal slave cylinder failure can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause fires, damage to surrounding components, and potentially harm the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Exhaust pipe making contact with gasoline tank
exhaust system becoming cherry red and catching on fire

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine manifold can cause fires, engine damage, and potentially harm the driver and passengers.
symptoms: engine manifold causing a fire while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the valve cover gasket can cause oil leaks, engine damage, and potentially harm the driver and passengers.
The stalling or rough idling of the vehicle can cause inconvenience, loss of transportation, and potentially harm the driver and passengers.
symptoms: difficulty diagnosing and repairing the issue
repeated attempts to correct the problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emergency brake release can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The parking brake releases by itself
the vehicle rolls or moves while parked
the emergency brake "pops off" or fails to engage
the vehicle experiences a sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling or hesitation of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates while driving
the vehicle stumbles or loses power
the engine cuts off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Fuses in Wiring Harness)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fuses in the wiring harness are not working

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the fire starts in the engine
